    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-11-14T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-11-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="519"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">680.84A/11–1452: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 519<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-11-14T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 14, 1952—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>795. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>s 776<note n="1" xml:id="d519fn1">
                        <ref target="#d513">Document 513</ref>.</note> and 786.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d519fn2">
                        <ref target="#d517">Document 517</ref>.</note> The Fon Min stated yesterday
                    morning that <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> is asking to be made eligible to
                    receive non-reimbursable as well as reimbursable mil aid. He urged an early and
                    favorable decision, saying that Israel is ready to join the US in preparing for
                    any eventuality. He made once more a point which has been made repeatedly by
                    spokesmen of the <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> to the effect that mil aid to
                    Israel cld be used to large extent for improvement of transportation and
                    communications facilities such as harbor works, roads and railroads having
                    strategic value.</p>
                <p>He said acceptance by Arab countries of Brit offer to supply jet fighters wld
                    result in need by Israel to acquire jet planes. He made it quite clear that
                    Israel does not wish to purchase the Brit planes offered but wld much prefer
                    Amer F–84 made jets. <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> wld like to obtain them
                    if possible through non-reimbursable mil aid, but if that not possible then at
                    “nominal price” on reimbursable basis (failing in either of these <gloss
                        target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> wld request US financial aid for purchase of Brit
                    jets).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DMB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
